'''Ciaran Fitzgerald''' (born [[4 June]] [[1952]]) is a former Irish rugby union footballer who played hooker. He captained Ireland to the [[Triple Crown (Rugby Union)|Triple Crown]] in 1983 and 1985, and the [[British and Irish Lions|British Lions]] on their losing tour to New Zealand in 1983. 

